public class VAnnotation
extends org.apache.uima.jcas.tcas.Annotation
A UIMA annotation that includes the display value and the original content value. Both are convienence features that will enable one to work directly with the annotation class rather than have to compute them. Updated by JCasGen Wed Aug 17 13:31:49 EDT 2022 XML source: C:/Users/divitag2/work/softwareRepos/bodyFunction/project/60_03_type-descriptors/target/jcasgen/typesystem.xml

    • getDisplayString

      public java.lang.String getDisplayString()
      getter for displayString - gets This is the "formatted" content between the begin and end span. There are cases where the content might have to be interpreted because it cannot be printed out (non-printing characters), or because the original content contains formatting chars (html formatting such as >. for <), or is a symbol that you might want to convert to ascii chars (copyright, trademark) This method is a convienence feature.
      Returns:
      value of the feature
